 Stella Damasus Stella Damasus has revealed on her Instagram page that her mother has passed on. The 43-year-old actress just celebrated the 11th anniversary of her father’s death in January 2021. The actress who announced her mother’s death shared a  picture of her mother with a caption that read “This is not goodbye, it’s TILL WE MEET AGAIN. Love you forever mummy.” Since the announcement on her page, her colleagues in the entertainment industry have flooded her page with condolence messages to console the grieving actress. Andrea Chika Chukwu wrote,  “Ooh dear God. I am so sorry sweetie sending you hugs and praying with you. May her soul rest in peace, Amen.” Shaffy Bello simply wrote, “My condolences darling.” While actress Halima Abubakar wrote, “Am so sorry sis.” Stella Damasus won the Award for Best Actress at the Nigeria Entertainment Awards in 2007. She was nominated for Best Actress in a Leading Role at the Africa Movie Academy Awards in 2009. In 2012, she won the award for Best Actress for the movie Two Brides and a Baby at the Golden Icons Academy Awards in Houston, Texas. The actress was born on April 24, 1978. Asides from acting, she is also a singer.